From: Ian Ray <ian.ray@gehealthcare.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Feb 2026 11:20:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] hwmon: (ina2xx) Add support for INA234 for kernel 6.6

INA234 is register compatible to INA226 (excepting manufacturer and die
or device id registers) but has different scaling.

The INA234 bus voltage register stores a 12-bit ADC result in bits[15:4]
with bits[3:0] always zero, giving an effective bus voltage LSB of 1.6 mV
per raw register bit (bus_voltage_shift=4, bus_voltage_lsb=25600 uV).
Without this patch, sensors bind as ina226 and read 1250 uV/bit instead of
1600 uV/bit — a systematic 22% underread on all bus voltages.

The power register coefficient for INA234 is 32 (vs 25 for INA226),
per TI datasheet equation: Power_W = 32 * Current_LSB * Power_reg_count.

Shunt voltage register format is identical to INA226 (shunt_div=400,
effective 2.5 uV per raw bit), so current and shunt measurements are
unaffected.

Alert attributes (ina226_group) are exposed since INA234 implements the
same MASK_ENABLE (0x06) and ALERT_LIMIT (0x07) registers as INA226.

Calibration value 2048 matches INA226 for optimal truncation-error
elimination (from TI INA234 datasheet eq. 3).

Adapted from upstream LKML patch v3 by Ian Ray <ian.ray@gehealthcare.com>
(Message-Id: 20260220112024.97446-4-ian.ray@gehealthcare.com) for the
kernel 6.6 ina2xx driver structure (older driver lacks ina260/sy24655).

Signed-off-by: Ian Ray <ian.ray@gehealthcare.com>
---
 drivers/hwmon/Kconfig  |  2 +-
 drivers/hwmon/ina2xx.c | 23 ++++++++++++++++++++---
 2 files changed, 21 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/hwmon/Kconfig b/drivers/hwmon/Kconfig
--- a/drivers/hwmon/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/hwmon/Kconfig
@@ -2018,7 +2018,7 @@ config SENSORS_INA2XX
 	select REGMAP_I2C
 	help
 	  If you say yes here you get support for INA219, INA220, INA226,
-	  INA230, and INA231 power monitor chips.
+	  INA230, INA231, and INA234 power monitor chips.
 
 	  The INA2xx driver is configured for the default configuration of
 	  the part as described in the datasheet.
diff --git a/drivers/hwmon/ina2xx.c b/drivers/hwmon/ina2xx.c
--- a/drivers/hwmon/ina2xx.c
+++ b/drivers/hwmon/ina2xx.c
@@ -98,7 +98,7 @@ static struct regmap_config ina2xx_regmap_config = {
 	.val_bits = 16,
 };
 
-enum ina2xx_ids { ina219, ina226 };
+enum ina2xx_ids { ina219, ina226, ina234 };
 
 struct ina2xx_config {
 	u16 config_default;
@@ -138,6 +138,15 @@ static const struct ina2xx_config ina2xx_config[] = {
 		.bus_voltage_lsb = 1250,
 		.power_lsb_factor = 25,
 	},
+	[ina234] = {
+		.config_default = INA226_CONFIG_DEFAULT,
+		.calibration_value = 2048,
+		.registers = INA226_REGISTERS,
+		.shunt_div = 400,		/* 2.5 uV/LSB raw ADC from INA2XX_SHUNT_VOLTAGE */
+		.bus_voltage_shift = 4,
+		.bus_voltage_lsb = 25600,	/* 25.6 mV/LSB; >>4 shift gives 1.6 mV effective */
+		.power_lsb_factor = 32,
+	},
 };
 
 /*
@@ -667,7 +676,7 @@ static int ina2xx_probe(struct i2c_client *client)
 	}
 
 	data->groups[group++] = &ina2xx_group;
-	if (chip == ina226)
+	if (chip == ina226 || chip == ina234)
 		data->groups[group++] = &ina226_group;
 
 	hwmon_dev = devm_hwmon_device_register_with_groups(dev, client->name,
@@ -687,6 +696,7 @@ static const struct i2c_device_id ina2xx_id[] = {
 	{ "ina226", ina226 },
 	{ "ina230", ina226 },
 	{ "ina231", ina226 },
+	{ "ina234", ina234 },
 	{ }
 };
 MODULE_DEVICE_TABLE(i2c, ina2xx_id);
@@ -712,6 +722,10 @@ static const struct of_device_id __maybe_unused ina2xx_of_match[] = {
 		.compatible = "ti,ina231",
 		.data = (void *)ina226
 	},
+	{
+		.compatible = "ti,ina234",
+		.data = (void *)ina234
+	},
 	{ },
 };
 MODULE_DEVICE_TABLE(of, ina2xx_of_match);
